general_exclusion_criteria:
History of persisting grade > 1 toxicity attributable to prior therapy (except mild alopecia, sensory neuropathy ≤grade 2);
Solid organ transplantation;
Concurrent enrolment in another investigational therapeutic trial;
Leptomeningeal disease;
Untreated or symptomatic central nervous system metastasis (treated brain metastases permissible if stable ≥4 weeks);
Active autoimmune disorders—including inflammatory bowel disease, rheumatoid arthritis, systemic scleroderma, systemic lupus erythematosus, ANCA-associated vasculitis, Guillain‑Barré syndrome, Myasthenia Gravis (other autoimmunity without immunosuppression allowable);
Clinically significant cardiovascular disease (recent stroke or myocardial infarction <6 months, congestive heart failure NYHA Class III–IV, unstable angina, uncontrolled arrhythmia);
Uncontrolled intercurrent serious infection or active psychiatric disorder limiting adherence;
Other concomitant malignant disease requiring active treatment or progressed within 2 years (excluding adequately treated basal/squamous skin cancer, superficial bladder cancer, localized prostate intraepithelial neoplasia, cervical carcinoma in situ, or other indolent tumors disease‑free >1 year);
Systemic glucocorticoids ≥10 mg/day prednisone-equivalent for non‑autoimmune indication within preceding 2 weeks;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Positive serology for human immunodeficiency virus;
Active hepatitis B core antigen-positive or hepatitis C RNA‑positive infection;
Known hypersensitivity to study‐product constituents or analogous biological products.

