Participants with Down syndrome;
participants with isolated extramedullary disease (extramedullary-only relapse);
participants with isolated central nervous system relapse or symptomatic CNS3 disease;
patients with acute promyelocytic leukemia;
patients with juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia;
malabsorption syndromes prohibiting oral drug intake;
use of proton pump inhibitors concurrently;
current participation in another investigational drug study;
known inherited bone‑marrow failure syndromes;
documented allergy to any protocol drugs;
active, uncontrolled infection at screening;
active, untreated HIV, hepatitis B, or hepatitis C infection;
pregnant or breastfeeding individuals;
pre‑existing disorders markedly increasing infection risk (e.g., cystic fibrosis, immune deficiencies, chronic neutropenia unrelated to leukemia);
significant congenital cardiovascular abnormalities (e.g., long QT syndrome, major structural defects);
conditions making study treatment unsafe or confounding toxicity evaluation;
hypersensitivity to fludarabine or cytarabine components;
receipt of live vaccination within the past six months.

