History of malignancy other than the enrolled cancer within three years before enrollment (exemptions: cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma, basal cell carcinoma, carcinoma in situ of the cervix, benign prostatic hypertrophy);
Presence of brain metastasis, leptomeningeal metastasis, or spinal cord compression;
Significant comorbidities such as uncontrolled cardiac disease, clinically meaningful respiratory compromise, impaired hepatic or renal function, active infections, or immunodeficiency disorders.

History of malignancy other than the enrolled cancer within three years before enrollment (exemptions: cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma, basal cell carcinoma, carcinoma in situ of the cervix, benign prostatic hypertrophy);
Presence of brain metastasis, leptomeningeal metastasis, or spinal cord compression;
Significant comorbidities such as uncontrolled cardiac disease, clinically meaningful respiratory compromise, impaired hepatic or renal function, active infections, or immunodeficiency disorders.

Participants receiving docetaxel who have metastatic castration‑resistant prostate cancer with anticipated time to next therapy < 12 months;
Unrecovered Grade > 1 toxicity from prior anticancer therapy (except alopecia);
Concurrent enrollment in another investigational study;
Brain metastases;
History of allergic reaction to study‑related compounds;
Symptomatic skeletal event (spinal cord compression, pathologic fracture, or recent (> 6 month) radiation/surgery to bone);
Uncontrolled pain attributable to prostate cancer or comorbid condition;
Visceral crisis indicating rapid disease progression with life expectancy < 18 months;
Uncontrolled intercurrent medical illnesses;
Second active malignant neoplasm;
Severe sleep disorders (e.g., narcolepsy);
Eye diseases impairing light transmission (untreated cataract, severe glaucoma, macular degeneration, blindness, pupillary abnormalities, retinal disorders);
Severe psychiatric impairment (bipolar disorder, mania);
Night‑shift occupational schedule;
Previous use of light therapy for fatigue/depression;
Recent intraocular surgery causing irritation (within 6 months);
Photosensitivity, epilepsy, or personal history of seizures.

Active or worsening pneumonia/pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease including New York Heart Association class III–IV heart failure;
Significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine clearance outside protocol limits);
Severe hepatic dysfunction exceeding protocol laboratory thresholds;
Untreated or rapidly evolving brain metastases;
Known human immunodeficiency virus infection or chronic hepatitis B/C infection;
Performance status worse than ECOG 1.

Fanconi anaemia;
Shwachman‑Diamond syndrome;
constitutional trisomy 21 or mosaic trisomy 21;
telomere biology disorders;
germline predisposition syndromes increasing toxicity risk;
concurrent malignant disease;
persistent left ventricular systolic dysfunction (ejection fraction \< 50%);
pregnancy;
lactation;
sexual activity without approved contraception;
history of severe organ dysfunction incompatible with intensive chemotherapy (uncontrolled hepatic, renal, pulmonary insufficiency);
unable to comply with study procedures or follow‑up.

