Patients with AJCC stage I or stage IVC (metastatic) disease or unresectable disease;
History of prior radiation and/or chemotherapy for head and neck cancer;
Any prior HER2‑directed therapy;
Active or uncontrolled infection;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illness such as symptomatic congestive heart failure, unstable angina, significant cardiac arrhythmia, or psychiatric conditions impairing protocol adherence;
Presence of another actively progressive malignancy requiring current treatment (excluding adequately treated basal/squamous skin cancer, in‑situ cervical cancer, or low‑risk prostate cancer on active surveillance);
Significant hepatic, renal, hematologic, or pulmonary impairment outside acceptable laboratory ranges.

History of pneumonitis or interstitial lung disease;
Uncontrolled congestive heart failure, myocardial infarction within past six months, left ventricular ejection fraction <50%;
Severe hepatic impairment (Child-Pugh C) or bilirubin > 2× upper limit normal;
Severe renal impairment (creatinine clearance <30 mL/min);
Active untreated or progressive central nervous system metastases;
Known active HIV infection, chronic hepatitis B or C infection;
Concurrent participation in another therapeutic investigational study;
Pregnancy, breastfeeding, or unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Performance status greater than Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score 1;
Other severe comorbidities precluding safe administration of study medication.

history of autoimmune disease (except isolated hypothyroidism, controlled type 1 diabetes, mild dermatitis/psoriasis/vitiligo meeting strict criteria);
active or past tuberculosis;
significant cardiovascular disease (New York Heart Association class II or worse, recent myocardial infarction, recent cerebrovascular event);
uncontrolled hypertension (systolic ≥ 150 mm Hg or diastolic ≥ 100 mm Hg despite therapy);
clinically significant bleeding disorders or current therapeutic anticoagulation;
moderate or severe ascites;
untreated or inadequately treated gastroesophageal varices;
recent serious infection or antibiotic use;
live attenuated vaccination within four weeks preceding study start;
severe hypersensitivity to monoclonal‑antibody components;
pregnancy, lactation, or inadequate contraception in persons of reproductive potential;
use of high‑dose aspirin (>325 mg/day), dual antiplatelet agents, or chronic high‑potency NSAIDs;
unstable neurological conditions unrelated to approved CNS metastasis rules.

History of prosthetic, breast, testicular or adrenal cancer (for solid‐tumour cohort);
Use of anabolic agents (testosterone, DHEA, growth hormone) within the past six months;
Hematocrit greater than 48%;
Serum creatinine greater than 2.5 mg/dL;
Prostatic specific antigen greater than 4 ng/mL or palpable nodules/on digital rectal examination;
Severe untreated obstructive sleep apnoea;
Uncontrolled congestive heart failure;
Myocardial infarction, acute coronary syndrome, cardiac revascularisation, stroke or arterial/thrombotic event within six months;
Known inherited thrombophilia (e.g., factor V Leiden);
Previous cerebrovascular accident leaving persistent neurological impairment;
Cognitive incapacity preventing informed consent (MMSE < 24);
Poorly controlled diabetes mellitus (HbA₁c > 10%);
Body mass index exceeding 40 kg/m²;
Bipolar disorder or schizophrenia.

