Active, progressive central nervous system metastases, leptomeningeal disease, or carcinomatous meningitis;
Concurrent infection with HIV, chronic hepatitis B, or chronic hepatitis C;
Other concurrent malignant disease requiring active therapy within three years preceding enrollment, except adequately treated basal/squamous cell skin cancer or cervical intraepithelial neoplasia;
Major surgical procedure or therapeutic radiation within four weeks of first study drug administration;
Any investigational product administered within four weeks prior to study entry;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Clinically significant ongoing gastrointestinal disorders affecting absorption (active ulcerative colitis, Crohn’s disease, severe malabsorption syndromes, prior extensive bowel resections).

