Any other primary malignant neoplasm within three years preceding enrollment (exceptions: non‑melanoma skin cancer, carcinoma in situ, low‑grade prostate cancer);
Known active primary central nervous system malignancy;
History of prior adoptive cellular or gene therapy, allogeneic stem cell transplantation, or solid organ transplantation;
Stroke or transient ischemic attack occurring within twelve months before enrollment;
Clinically significant cardiovascular disease within six months before enrollment or any prior episode of congestive heart failure;
Severe immediate hypersensitivity reactions to cyclophosphamide, fludarabine, recombinant interleukin‑2, methotrexate, gentamicin, or other aminoglycoside antibiotics;
Presence of any primary immunodeficiency disorder;
Receipt of a live attenuated vaccine within four weeks prior to enrollment or intention to receive a live vaccine before lymphodepletive conditioning or administration of NT‑175;
Active autoimmune or inflammatory condition necessitating chronic systemic corticosteroids or other immunosuppressants (exception made for residual effects of prior checkpoint inhibitors);
Females of childbearing potential who are currently nursing, breastfeeding, or unwilling to employ effective contraceptive measures throughout the study duration;
Documented diagnosis of Li‑Fraumeni syndrome in the participant or first-degree relative.

