Clinically significant cardiovascular, vascular, gastrointestinal, inflammatory, or pulmonary disease;
Active acute viral, bacterial, or systemic fungal infection requiring intravenous therapy;
Receipt of a live attenuated vaccine within four weeks prior to dosing;
Known HIV positivity or chronic hepatitis B/C with uncontrolled disease;
Second primary invasive malignancy not in remission for at least twelve months (excluding certain low‑risk lesions);
Pregnancy, planned pregnancy, or breastfeeding;
Untreated or inadequately treated hepatic metastases lacking stability for three months.

History of stage IV (metastatic) breast cancer or any prior invasive breast cancer (ipsilateral or contralateral);
Myocardial infarction or unstable angina within six months of enrolment;
Serious ventricular arrhythmia, high‑grade AV block, other major cardiac arrhythmias, or left ventricular ejection fraction less than 50%;
Active serious infections requiring systemic antimicrobials;
Uncontrolled central nervous system involvement or symptomatic brain metastases;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Concurrent participation in another interventional therapeutic trial;
Significant hepatic impairment (bilirubin > 2× ULN or AST/ALT > 5× ULN);
Severe renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance <30 mL/min);
Performance status worse than ECOG 1.
